      "content": "Asking about hobbies like skiing or after-work drinks can backfire if candidates interpret these as expectations, so instead probe their social preferences by asking which activities truly recharger them and who they would enjoy doing it with. Since you value spending time together, consider inviting everyone for an early round informal group activity where they can demonstrate their natural social style naturally, such as going for drinks or a run. If a candidate seems visually passing, filter heavily on whether they volunteer for social events—which rarely requires extra effort—and how they interact with personality types different from their own. Ultimately, look for candidates who provide empathy and seem genuinely comfortable in your specific social circle rather than just agreeing to join it.",
